The paper discusses the development of a hybrid architecture for instructing grasping tasks by man-machine interaction, which involves combining statistical methods, neural networks, and finite state machines. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of visual perception and speech recognition, which are common topics in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), respectively. The paper also mentions the need for cognitive abilities in robots, which is a topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of making the system effective and convenient for the user, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
